    "title": "How to include App Link in Share-Intent feature in Android",
    "body": "<p>I created an android app and suceeded in adding share button and it works great. But the only challenge I'm having now is how to include app download link along side with the textView generated for sharing.<br>\nFor example\nI want to have something like this:</p>\n\n<p>Baby soap that nurtures skin\nis the recommended soap\nfor skin care and viral\ntreatment etc. <em>This App can be downloaded from <a href=\"https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id</a></em></p>\n\n<p><strong>This is my Share Java Code</strong></p>\n\n<pre><code>                Intent sendIntent = new Intent();\n                sendIntent.setAction(Intent.ACTION_SEND);\n                sendIntent.putExtra(Intent.EXTRA_TEXT, mDetailTv.getText().toString());\n                sendIntent.setType(\"text/plain\");\n                Intent.createChooser(sendIntent, \"Share via\");\n                startActivity(sendIntent);```\n\n\n\n**This is what i tried that didn't work**\n\n//share Copied Text characters via other apps button\n                Intent sendIntent = new Intent();\n                sendIntent.setAction(Intent.ACTION_SEND);\n                sendIntent.putExtra(Intent.EXTRA_TEXT, mDetailTv.getText().toString());\n                sendIntent.putExtra(Intent.EXTRA_SUBJECT, \"Check out the App at: https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=\"+\"app_package_name\");\n                sendIntent.setType(\"text/plain\");\n                Intent.createChooser(sendIntent, \"Share via\");\n                startActivity(sendIntent);\n\n</code></pre>\n"
